QueryData

Represents Data returned from a query a a list of name/value pairs.

metadata.name: total_bytes
title: Gcloud
Bigquery
QueryData#total_bytes
metadata.description: The total number of bytes processed for this query.

metadata.name: complete?
title: Gcloud
Bigquery
QueryData#complete?
metadata.description: Whether the query has completed or not. When data is present this will always be true. When false, total will not be available.

metadata.name: cache_hit?
title: Gcloud
Bigquery
QueryData#cache_hit?
metadata.description: Whether the query result was fetched from the query cache.

metadata.name: headers
title: Gcloud
Bigquery
QueryData#headers
metadata.description: The name of the columns in the data.

metadata.name: next?
title: Gcloud
Bigquery
QueryData#next?
metadata.description: Is there a next page of data?

metadata.name: job
title: Gcloud
Bigquery
QueryData#job
metadata.description: The BigQuery Job that was created to run the query.
